        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>filmmaking processes and techniques [300263876], filmmaking and filmmaking processes and techniques [300263875], image-making processes and techniques [300053159], processes and techniques by specific type [300053003], Processes and Techniques (hierarchy name) [300053001], Activities Facet [300264090]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Unusual elements of a motion picture created using a variety of techniques such as computer, mechanical, makeup, pyrotechnic, optical, lighting, camera speed, weather effects, and model techniques. Generally they are used to create effects that normal camera techniques or set action cannot provide or would be too costly to shoot normally. They are often inserted into the motion picture by the special effects department after live shooting.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Los elementos inusuales de una película crearon una variedad de técnicas como las realizadas por computadora, mecánicas, maquillajes, ópticas, velocidad de la cámara fotográfica, efectos del tiempo, y las técnicas del modelo.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ongewone filmelementen die tot stand worden gebracht met behulp van diverse technieken, bijvoorbeeld computer-, mechanische, grime-, pyrotechnische, optische, licht-, draaisnelheids-, weers- en modelleertechnieken. Ze worden doorgaans gebruikt om effecten te creëren die met normale cameratechnieken of acteerhandelingen niet bereikt kunnen worden of daarvoor te kostbaar zouden zijn. Ze worden vaak in de setbeelden gemonteerd door een aparte speciale-effectenafdeling.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>電影中利用如電腦、機械、化妝、煙火、光學、燈光、攝影速度、天氣效果以及模型等多種技術，所製作出來的特殊元素。一般而言，特殊效果是用來製出一般攝影技術或拍攝現場無法提供，或以一般拍攝方式會導致成本過高的效果。通常是由特殊效果部門在實際拍攝之後置入電影中。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Elementos incomuns de um filme criado usando uma variedade de técnicas, como computador, mecânica, maquiagem, pirotécnica, óptica, iluminação, velocidade da câmera, efeitos climáticos e técnicas de modelo. Geralmente, eles são usados para criar efeitos que as técnicas normais de câmera ou ação definida não podem fornecer ou seriam muito caros para filmar normalmente. Eles são frequentemente inseridos no filme pelo departamento de efeitos especiais após a filmagem ao vivo.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
